==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fainant
<hw>fai`n⟦eacute⟧`ant"</hw></mhw>
<pr>(f⟦asl⟧`n⟦asl⟧`⟦aum⟧N")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.;
<ets>fait</ets> he does + <ets>n⟦eacute⟧ant</ets> nothing.]</ety>
<def>Doing nothing; shiftless; disinclined to work or
exertion.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bone-idle, bone-lazy, do-nothing(prenominal),
indolent, lazy, otiose, shiftless, slothful, workshy,
work-shy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>faineant</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>faineant</ent>⟦br⟧
